    "title": {
      "rendered": "8 Fundraising Tools to Watch in 2016"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/8-Fundraising-Tools-to-Watch-in-2016-Facebook.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19099\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-19099\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/8-Fundraising-Tools-to-Watch-in-2016-Facebook-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"8 Fundraising Tools to Watch in 2016 Facebook\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/8-Fundraising-Tools-to-Watch-in-2016-Facebook.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/8-Fundraising-Tools-to-Watch-in-2016-Facebook.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/8-Fundraising-Tools-to-Watch-in-2016-Facebook.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/8-Fundraising-Tools-to-Watch-in-2016-Facebook.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/8-Fundraising-Tools-to-Watch-in-2016-Facebook.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><em>2016 is going to be a big year for mobile and digital wallet payments.</em> Apple, Facebook, Twitter, Google, PayPal, and Amazon are scrambling to be your chosen first choice and while this is predominantly playing out in the consumer market, in 2016 we will finally start to see mobile and digital wallet payments\u00a0impact\u00a0online fundraising in the nonprofit sector.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">We&#8217;re also getting close to a new generation of mobile fundraising apps that are sustainable and have long term appeal to donors (<em>think:</em> giving portfolio, gamification, and one-tap, finger scan giving). That said, fundraising tools come and go and long-term financial sustainability is tough for social good entrepreneurs to achieve (<em>muchos kudos</em> for trying), but the fundraising tools list for 2016 (<strong><a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2015/04/11/9-fundraising-tools-to-watch-in-2015/\">view the 2015 list</a></strong>) represent eight ideas whose time have come in the nonprofit sector.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">1. Apple Pay<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.apple.com/apple-pay/\" target=\"_blank\">apple.com/apple-pay</a></h2>\n<p>In addition to paying for goods and services in stores, Apply Pay enables\u00a0iPhone and iPad users to make payments with a tap and a finger scan. The service will likely be adopted by many fundraising service providers in 2016 with <strong><a href=\"http://crowdster.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Crowdster for Nonprofits</a></strong> being one of the first.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.apple.com/apple-pay/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19077\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19077\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Apple-Pay.png?resize=600%2C407\" alt=\"Apple Pay\" width=\"600\" height=\"407\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Apple-Pay.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Apple-Pay.png?resize=300%2C204&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">2. Facebook Fundraisers and Donate Buttons<br />\n<a href=\"https://donations.fb.com/\" target=\"_blank\">donations.fb.com</a></h2>\n<p>&#8220;Fundraisers&#8221; are pages where <em>verified and approved\u00a0nonprofits</em> can raise money for specific fundraising campaigns and &#8220;Donate&#8221; buttons enable nonprofits to accept donations inside of Facebook directly from their Page and posts.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://donations.fb.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19074\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19074\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/facebook-fundraisers-and-donate-now-buttons.jpg?resize=600%2C268\" alt=\"facebook fundraisers and donate now buttons\" width=\"600\" height=\"268\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/facebook-fundraisers-and-donate-now-buttons.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/facebook-fundraisers-and-donate-now-buttons.jpg?resize=300%2C134&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">3. Give A Dime<br />\n<a href=\"https://giveadime.org/\" target=\"_blank\">giveadime.org</a></h2>\n<p>A service that\u00a0rounds up\u00a0your credit or debit card purchases to the nearest dollar and then donates the funds raised to your chosen charity.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://giveadime.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19071\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19071\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Give-A-Dime-2.png?resize=600%2C284\" alt=\"Give A Dime 2\" width=\"600\" height=\"284\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Give-A-Dime-2.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Give-A-Dime-2.png?resize=300%2C142&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">4. Givelocity<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.givelocity.com/\" target=\"_blank\">givelocity.com</a></h2>\n<p>A\u00a0platform that enables individuals to create groups where members donate $1 (minimum donation)\u00a0and vote each month on which nonprofit will receive the lump sum.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.givelocity.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19090\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19090\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Givelocity.png?resize=600%2C329\" alt=\"Givelocity\" width=\"600\" height=\"329\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Givelocity.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Givelocity.png?resize=300%2C165&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">5. Givolio<br />\n<a href=\"http://givolio.com/\" target=\"_blank\">givolio.com</a></h2>\n<p>A mobile app that enables donors to donate to their favorite nonprofit in just a few taps. Donors can build a giving portfolio, view their giving history, and receive tax reports via email.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://givolio.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19080\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19080\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Givolio.jpg?resize=600%2C289\" alt=\"Givolio\" width=\"600\" height=\"289\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Givolio.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Givolio.jpg?resize=300%2C145&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">6. Omaze<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.omaze.com/\" target=\"_blank\">omaze.com</a></h2>\n<p>A website that encourages individuals to donate in order to win once-in-a-lifetime experiences.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.omaze.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19086\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19086\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Omaze.png?resize=600%2C270\" alt=\"Omaze\" width=\"600\" height=\"270\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Omaze.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Omaze.png?resize=300%2C135&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">7. Pledgeling<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.pledgeling.com/enterprise/\" target=\"_blank\">pledgeling.com</a></h2>\n<p>A service that allows businesses to easily set up an employee giving program.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.pledgeling.com/enterprise/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19084\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19084\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Pledgeling.png?resize=600%2C290\" alt=\"Pledgeling\" width=\"600\" height=\"290\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Pledgeling.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Pledgeling.png?resize=300%2C145&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">8. YouGiveGoods<br />\n<a href=\"https://yougivegoods.com\" target=\"_blank\">yougivegoods.com</a></h2>\n<p>A platform that enables individuals, businesses, and nonprofits to create online food and supply drives.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://yougivegoods.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19089\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19089\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/YouGiveGoods.png?resize=600%2C338\" alt=\"YouGiveGoods\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/YouGiveGoods.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/YouGiveGoods.png?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 17px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold;\"><em>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</em></span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-16024\" style=\"margin: 10px; border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/mobile-for-good-look-inside.jpg?resize=99%2C150\" alt=\"mobile for good look inside\" width=\"99\" height=\"150\" /></a>Based on more than 20 years of experience and 25,000+ hours spent utilizing mobile and social media, <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\" target=\"_blank\"><em><strong>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</strong></em></a> is a comprehensive 256-page book packed with more than 500 best practices. Written on the premise that all communications and fundraising are now mobile and social, Mobile for Good is a step-by-step how-to guide for writing, implementing, and maintaining a mobile and social fundraising strategy for your nonprofit.</p>\n",
